1. Blanch Maggi 2-minute curry noodles without seasoning for 1 minute. Toss.
2. Stir fry onion, qarlic, squid and prawn (optional) till fragrant.
3. Add water, 1 and half pack of MAGGI 2-Minute Curry Seasoning and mustard leaves. Stir evenly, cook till gravy chages colour.
4. Bring to a boil, then pour the egg slowly into the gravy.
5. Turn off the fire and let it sit, stir it a little before serving.
6. Pour gravy over boiled MAGGI noodles. Serve.